<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Verify left margin for non-replaced block level element in normal flow</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify margin-left on non-replaced block element is applied." />
        <style type="text/css">
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
            }
            #d1
            {
                margin-left: 10px;
                border: solid black 1px;
                background-color: green;
            }
            #d2
            {
                width: 10px;
                height: 20px;
                background-color: blue;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the left edge of the green box is aligned with the right edge of the blue box and the bottom edge of the green box is aligned with the top edge of the blue box.</p>
        <div id="d1">ContentFiller</div>
        <div id="d2"></div>
    </body>
</html>